The Apple iPhone 13 is the ultimate smartphone for business, and you can now upgrade your enterprise’s entire fleet to this excellent device through iStore Business. The iStore Business upgrade service allows businesses to ensure that their employees are equipped with the best 5G smartphones on the market from just R199 per month. Learn more about the benefits of an iPhone 13 fleet. We unpack how to take advantage of the iStore Business upgrade service, below. iStore Business’s fleet upgrade service allows your company to centralize the purchasing and management of its Apple iPhone fleet. All you need to do is visit iStore Business and enter your company details – including its number of employees, years in operation, and annual turnover. An iStore Business consultant will then get in touch with you to assist your business with tailored packages while also making your fleet upgrade process as efficient as possible. You will also get the most out of your iPhone fleet with free iCare Plus and comprehensive technical support that comprises user training, migration assistance, and more. iCare Plus is available exclusively from iStore Business and gives you peace of mind by including an Apple Authorised screen repair valued at R1,999 and a 24-month extended warranty on the iPhones. Several payment options are available from iStore Business and you can choose the plan that best suits your financial strategy. You can either trade-in your existing iPhone models or start your journey with brand-new iPhone 13 smartphones. Your options include: Trade-in from R7,390 – When you trade in an iPhone 11 valued at R8,500.
Rent an iPhone 13 from R199 per month for 36 months – When you trade in an iPhone 11 valued at R8,500.
New fleet without trade-in from R15,216 per smartphone. These prices exclude VAT, and you can begin your fleet with just five iPhone 13 smartphones. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-585586 size-full" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/In-article-Image-iStire-iPhone-13-May-2022.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/In-article-Image-iStire-iPhone-13-May-2022.jpg 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/In-article-Image-iStire-iPhone-13-May-2022-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> With a team of iPhone 13-equipped employees, you can ensure everyone is using superfast 5G connectivity that allows them to download, upload, and share files while seamlessly connecting with colleagues through high-quality video conferencing. The iPhone 13 is also packs the powerful A15 Bionic chip for supercharged productivity – and this is complemented by an incredible battery life that ensures your employees can stay connected all day with up to 19 hours of video playback. It is then furnished with a Focus Mode that lets employees get work done without distractions, and you can stay organised and collaborate with Notes. Additionally, businesses will benefit from the iPhone 13’s built-in security features that keep your essential data secure and control what information employees share. Learn more about the benefits of an iPhone 13 fleet.